summary: This API is used to retrieve the inbound order details including the planned inbound detail, actual inbound detail and inbound status, etc
description:
This API is used to retrieve the inbound order details including the planned inbound detail, actual inbound detail and inbound status, etc. Version
202409
  
API Testing Tool

query.description: Use this property to pass shop information in requesting the API. Failure in passing the correct value when requesting the API for cross-border shops will return incorrect response.  Get by API Get Authorization Shop
Every single app will have a unique key. Please use the specific key assigned to your app.
Signature generated by gen algorithm. When you send API requests to TTS, you must sign them so that TTS can identify the senders.
Unix timestamp GMT (UTC+00:00). This timestamp is used across all API requests. Developers can use this convert to local time.

A list of inbound order IDs needs to be queried. The API will return the inbound order information for these IDs. Note: The inbound ID consists of a series of numbers without the "IBR" prefix. You can get the value in data.inbound_order_id in Inbound FBT order status change webhook or in data.inventory_records.order.id in the response of Search FBT Inventory Record.

header.description: The seller access_token value from Get Access Token, when user_type = 0. Follow this guide to get seller access_token.

schema.description: The success or failure status code returned in API response.
The success or failure messages returned in API response. Reasons of failure will be described in the message.

children.description: A list of inbound order detail information.
The identifier for inbound order generated in Fillfilled by TikTok system.
The inbound order type. Possible values: - REPLENISHMENT
Merchant information.
The identifier of the merchant in Fulfilled by TikTok system.
The merchant name.
The time when the inbound order created. Unix timestamp in seconds.
The time when the inbound order shipped. Unix timestamp in seconds.
The expected arrival time provided by merchant. Unix timestamp in seconds.
The actual arrival time. Unix timestamp in seconds.
The warehouse information.
The Identifier for warehouse generated by Fulfilled by TikTok system.
The identifier for warehouse generated by TikTok Shop system, will have the relationship with fbt_warehouse_id.
The Fulfilled by TikTok warehouse name.
The Fullfilled by TikTok warehouse type.  Possible values: - PLATFORM_WAREHOUSE
A list of planned goods details in the inbound order.
The identifier for goods generated by Fulfilled by TikTok system.
The identifier for goods defined by merchant.
The Fulfilled by TikTok goods name.
The planned goods quantity.
The identifier for Stock Keeping Unit (SKU) generated by Fulfilled by TikTok system.
A list of actual received inbound order batch details.
The identifier for inbound put away batch.
The identifier for goods generated by Fulfilled by TikTok system.
The quantity of normal goods in the inbound order batch.
The quantity of defective goods in the inbound order batch.
A list of product identifiers generated by TikTok Shop, which will be empty if the current goods do not match any product.
A list of SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) identifiers generated by TikTok Shop, which will be empty if the current goods do not match any SKU.
The total number of units received by the Fulfilled by TikTok warehouse in the inbound order batch, which is the sum of normal_quantity and defective_quantity.
A list of inbound order operation history.
The time when the inbound order is processed by the merchant or warehouses, represented as a Unix timestamp in seconds.

The order status in Fulfilled by TikTok warehouse. Possible values: - WORKING - READY_TO_SHIP - TO_BE_RECEIVED - ARRIVED_HUB - INTERNAL_TRANSFER - RECEIVING - PARTIALLY_RECEIVED - RECEIVED - CANCELLED - DELIVERED
A list of carrier information.
The carrier name.
The tracking number for the current inbound shipment with the carrier.
